    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1975-12-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1975-12-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="165"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d165">
                <head>165. Memorandum From Director of Central Intelligence <persName
                        corresp="#p_CWE_1" type="from">Colby</persName> to Secretary of State
                        <persName corresp="#p_KHA_1" type="to">Kissinger</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d165fn1">Source: Library of Congress,
                        Manuscript Division, <persName corresp="#p_KHA_1">Kissinger</persName>
                        Papers, Box CL 103, Geopolitical File, Angola Chronological File. Secret;
                        Sensitive; Eyes Only. A note that reads “Urgent” is attached to the
                        memorandum. A copy was sent to <persName corresp="#p_SBC_1"
                            >Scowcroft</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1975-12-23">December 23, 1975</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>South African Decision to Withdraw from Angola</item>
                </list>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>[<hi rend="italic">1½ lines not declassified</hi>] the South African
                        National Security Council decided on the evening of 23 December to withdraw
                        South African troops from Angola. The timing of the withdrawal is not
                        definite pending consultations beginning 24 December with the National Front
                        for the Liberation of Angola (<gloss target="#t_FNLA_1">FNLA</gloss>), the
                        National Union for the Total Independence of Angola (<gloss
                            target="#t_UNITA_1">UNITA</gloss>), and possibly with President
                            <persName corresp="#p_MSS_1">Mobutu</persName>. [<hi rend="italic">1½
                            lines not declassified</hi>] emphasized that the withdrawal will be
                        orderly, and that the service hoped to obtain the concurrence of the <gloss
                            target="#t_FNLA_1">FNLA</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_UNITA_1"
                            >UNITA</gloss>.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>[<hi rend="italic">less than 1 line not declassified</hi>] the South
                        Africans probably intend to withdraw before the Organization of African
                        Unity (<gloss target="#t_OAU_1">OAU</gloss>) meeting now scheduled for the
                        second week in January. By withdrawing before the <gloss target="#t_OAU_1"
                            >OAU</gloss> meeting, the South Africans hope that <gloss
                            target="#t_UNITA_1">UNITA</gloss> and the <gloss target="#t_FNLA_1"
                            >FNLA</gloss> will be free to deny the presence of South Africans in
                        Angola and to invite on-site inspection. The South African withdrawal
                        timetable might be adjusted, depending upon the results of consultations
                        with the <gloss target="#t_FNLA_1">FNLA</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_UNITA_1"
                            >UNITA</gloss> and President <persName corresp="#p_MSS_1"
                            >Mobutu</persName>.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CWE_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">W.E. Colby</hi>
                        </persName>
                        <note n="2" xml:id="d165fn2">David H. Blee signed for <persName
                                corresp="#p_CWE_1">Colby</persName> above <persName
                                corresp="#p_CWE_1">Colby</persName>’s typed signature.</note>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
